One of the biggest questions he has not figured out is why every song must end. Apparently that’s what a lot of people want when they go to rock shows now, and if you don’t do it, people think you are awful. He doesn’t really buy into that, and doing so denies the idea that an entire set can be delicate and subtle and loud and powerful all at once. This is not, after all, a pissing contest.

KO is touring a new record called Twelve in the Hive (available at cdbaby.com). You can contact him at ConradOtterman@hotmail.com to arrange booking. Look for us playing some Nirvana covers with Blind Mice at Tio Leo’s on December 13. More details later.
